      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, March 14.-The two\nmonths embargo on freight, intend\ned for the eastern market, which\nthrew nearly 100000 men out of\nemployment, closed down hundreds\nof lumber and shingle mills and all\nbut paralyzed scores Of enterprises\nthrough Seattle and the Northwest.\nis lifted.\n\n\nPursuant to the order issued\nyesterday by General Manager e.\ne. Ward, the Great Northern &C\ncepted ftranscontinental shipments\nthis morning for the first time since\nJan. IT.\n\n\nSimilar action, 1t is announced,\nwill be taken by the Union Pacific\nsystem within 10 days.\n\n\nFully 5000 men will return tc\nwork as a result today in the i'm\nmediate vicinity of Seattle and its\nsurrounding cities."
